The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Md. Sp. trounce Tolly 3-0 
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Mohammedan Sporting beat Tollygunge Agragami 3-0 in the All-Airlines Gold Cup football tournament in Haldia on Thursday. Nigerian striker John Ugwu, Dipendu Biswas and Syed Rahim Nabi were the scorers, according to information received here. The first half ended goalless. Ugwu put Mohammedan Sporting ahead with a powerful left-footer midway through the second session. Dipendu then struck following a pass from Abdul Rouf Khan. Nabi put the finishing touches, capitalising on a free-kick by Ugwu. Mohammedan Sportings Momocha Singh suffered a shin bone injury and was shifted to a city nursing home later. Tollygunges Akeem Abolanle was also admitted to a hospital after he crashed into the billboards on the sidelines.  Thais beat India Meanwhile, in Bangkok, the Thailand national team defeated India 2-0 in a preparatory match for the forthcoming Afro-Asian Games in Bangkok on Thursday. According to information received here, the teams were locked goalless at the breather. The Indians were earlier held goalless by an under-23 Thailand side.  Copyright 
